title: Bella Thorne cuddles up to Nat Wolff in LA
text:
Her love life has captured the attention of many over after she was wrongly accused by fans of cheating on her ex-boyfriend Tyler Posey with singer Charlie Puth.
And it appears Bella Thorne is moving on from the drama as she enjoyed a lunch date with Paper Towns actor Nat Wolff on Sunday in Los Angeles.
The 19-year-old - who is set to star in Freeform's Famous in Love - put on a cosy display with the 22-year-old star, who is known for his roles in The Fault In Our Stars and The Intern.
Scroll down for video
Catching up: It appears Bella Thorne is moving on from the drama as she enjoyed a lunch date with Paper Towns actor Nat Wolff on Sunday in Los Angeles
Bella opted to flaunt her taut stomach for the day time outing as she slipped into a skintight white tummy teasing top.
Accentuating her toned torso, she slipped on a pair of ripped knee grey washed denims that showcased her toned pins as she left the eatery hinting at her printed intimate's waistband.
She attempted to combat the Californian chill in an oversized black baseball shirt as sauntered to her waiting car in a pair of Union Jack embellished Doc Martins.
Leaving her blue hued locks loose, she appeared comfortable in Nat's company as they shared a sweet embrace following their time together.
MailOnline have contacted Bella Thorne and Nat Wolff's reps for comment.

Comfortable: Leaving her blue hued locks loose, she appeared comfortable in Nat's company as they shared left the LA eatery
The former Disney starlet, who has 14.7 million followers on I nstagram , said she'd been cyberbullied after she split from Tyler Posey, 25, and immediately was photographed with Charlie Puth.
Thorne said her followers thought - wrongly - that she'd cheated on Teen Wolf star Posey, whom she dated after the end in August of her year-long romance with actor Gregg Sulkin, with singer Puth, 25.
'I was getting death threats for a hot minute because they thought I had cheated on my ex, which is a total lie,' she told the magazine.
'When I woke up that morning — it f***ing sucks,' she said. 'It doesn’t feel good to think that everybody in the world just thinks you’re an absolutely disgusting person and just because I’m somebody where people know my name, it’s so much worse for me.'
Brief romances: Thorne said she'd been cyberbullied after she split from Teen Wolf star Tyler Posey, 25 and immediately was photographed with singer Charlie Puth, (pictured above)
She dated Posey from September until early December followed by a short romance with Puth.
The Shake It Up actress - who previously dated Gregg Sulkin - explained she has been deeply affected by the negative backlash she received.
'People take social media as such a big thing. And they all think they know what they’re talking about,' Thorne said.
'And they think they know your life and they get their friends to trash you. And they get all these people to hate on you and call you whatever names in the book. It’s kind of like one person says it and then everybody jumps on it.'
Over: Gregg Sulkin and Bella dated for a year before going their separate ways in 2016
